<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-21T01:13:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-21T01:13:00-05:00" n="471" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d471">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/5445: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Vladivostok</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MDB1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Macgowan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Vladivostok</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-21T15:00:00+08:47"><hi rend="italic">October 21,
                                        1919, 3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 6:25
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>558. O’Reilly, Acting British High Commissioner, today informed me he had
                            been recalled urgently on account of his attitude toward <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName>, which I was criticising.
                            Repeated to Tokyo and Omsk.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_MDB1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Macgowan</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>